---
import Link from "../../components/Link.astro";
import Highlight from "../../components/Highlight.astro";
---

<p class="intro">
  Projects are never finished, but they are always in progress. Here are some of my projects as a developer.
</p>

<div class="project">
  <h3>
    <Link href="https://black-atom.industries" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Black Atom Industries</Link>
  </h3>
  <p>Open-source theming system with 27+ themes across many platforms (Neovim, Zed, Ghostty, WezTerm, Tmux, and more).</p>
  <p>
    Built with an <Highlight>adapter pattern</Highlight>
    for consistent theme generation from a central source using <Highlight>OKLCH color space</Highlight>.
  </p>
  <p>Maintained with focus on developer experience and cross-platform consistency.</p>
</div>

<div class="project">
  <h3>
    <Link href="https://github.com/nikbrunner/awdcs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">AWDCS</Link>
  </h3>
  <p>
    Scope-based keymap architecture for modal editors organizing bindings by operational context (App, Workspace, Document,
    Change, Symbol) rather than tool-specific functions.
  </p>
  <p>
    Features <Highlight>systematic prefix patterns</Highlight> and
    <Highlight>semantic naming</Highlight> for consistent, memorable keybindings across workflows.
  </p>
</div>

<style>
  .intro {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--fg-support);
  }

  h3 {
    background-color: var(--bg-support);
    padding: var(--size-2) var(--size-4);
    border-radius: var(--radius-2);
    border: var(--border-size-2) solid var(--fg-accent);
  }

  .project p:first-of-type {
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-9);
  }
</style>
